Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me create a summary report with all the findings.

## Summary of RFQ Feature Investigation

I have thoroughly searched the designflow-frontend repository and identified the exact locations and status of both bugs. Here are my findings:

### BUG #1: Missing "Select All" Checkbox for RFQ Groupings

**Status:** The "select all" checkbox functionality was **intentionally removed** in commit `8afbdcec` (May 18, 2026) as part of an AG Grid v32→v35 API migration cleanup.

**History:**
- **Added** in commit `a4560b8c` (May 23, 2022) with initial reminder feature
- **Re-added** in commit `b63beb8e` (Jan 26, 2026) after being removed
- **Removed again** in commit `8afbdcec` (May 18, 2026) during the AG Grid deprecation sweep

**Current Configuration:**
- **File:** `C:\repos\dflow plm\designflow-frontend\src\app\pages\rfq\rfq.component.ts`
- **Lines 266-273:** Row selection configuration
  ```typescript
  rowSelection: {
    mode: 'multiRow',
    checkboxes: true,
    checkboxLocation: 'autoGroupColumn',
    headerCheckbox: false,           // ← HEADER CHECKBOX DISABLED
    enableClickSelection: false,
    groupSelects: 'descendants'
  }
  ```

**What was removed:**
- **Line 893-894** (old code, now removed): `colHeaders[i].headerCheckboxSelection = true;` on the price_code column
- **Line ~227** (old code, now removed): Function-based `headerCheckboxSelection` in `defaultColDef` that used `isFirstColumn()` callback

**Impact:** Users can still select individual rows by clicking their checkboxes in the auto-group column, but there is no header checkbox to select all visible rows at once.

---

### BUG #2: Reminder Button Not Sending & No Toast Confirmation Appearing

**Status:** The reminder functionality **is present and appears to be working**, but there may be a missing toast notification in certain conditions OR an API call failure.

**Relevant Code Locations:**

1. **Reminder Button Handler:**
   - **File:** `C:\repos\dflow plm\designflow-frontend\src\app\pages\rfq\rfq.component.ts`
   - **Lines 3915-3946:** `onReminder()` method

   ```typescript
   async onReminder() {
     let selectedRowData = this.gridApi.getSelectedNodes();
     const sentVendors = new Set(); // ✅ Track vendor IDs to avoid duplicates

     for (var i = 0; selectedRowData.length > i; i++) {
       if (selectedRowData[i].data) {
         if (selectedRowData[i].data.Vendors) {
           for (var j = 0; selectedRowData[i].data.Vendors.length > j; j++) {
             if (selectedRowData[i].data.Vendors[j].req_status == null) {
               const vendor = selectedRowData[i].data.Vendors[j].Vendor;
               const vendorId = vendor?.id;

               // ✅ Skip if this vendor was already emailed
               if (sentVendors.has(vendorId)) continue;
               sentVendors.add(vendorId);

               await firstValueFrom(this.itemService
                 .sendPriceReq({
                   id: vendorId,
                   rfqItem_priceCode: selectedRowData[i].data.Vendors[j].priceCode,
                   sendEmail: true,
                 }));
             }
           }
         }
       }
     }

     this._snackBar.open('Reminder was sent successfully.', 'ok', {
       duration: 2000,
     });
   }
   ```

2. **Reminder Button UI Visibility:**
   - **File:** `C:\repos\dflow plm\designflow-frontend\src\app\pages\rfq\rfq.component.html`
   - **Lines 16-24:** Button render condition

   ```html
   @if (ReminderSelectVisiblity) {
     <button
       mat-stroked-button
       class="secondary-btn"
       (click)="onReminder()">
       <mat-icon>notifications</mat-icon>
       <span>Reminder</span>
     </button>
   }
   ```

3. **Reminder Button Visibility Toggle:**
   - **File:** `C:\repos\dflow plm\designflow-frontend\src\app\pages\rfq\rfq.component.ts`
   - **Line 135:** Property declaration: `ReminderSelectVisiblity: boolean = false;`
   - **Lines 2638-2653:** `onSelectionChanged()` method that controls visibility

   ```typescript
   onSelectionChanged(event: SelectionChangedEvent) {
     const selectedRows = this.getSelectedRfqRows();

     if (selectedRows.length > 1) {
       this.multiSelectVisiblity = true;
     } else {
       this.multiSelectVisiblity = false;
     }
     this.addFactoriesSelectVisibility = selectedRows.length > 0;

     if (selectedRows.length > 0) {
       this.ReminderSelectVisiblity = true;
     } else {
       this.ReminderSelectVisiblity = false;
     }
   }
   ```

4. **Service Call:**
   - **File:** `C:\repos\dflow plm\designflow-frontend\src\app\helpers\services\main.service.ts`
   - **Lines 141-142:** API endpoint

   ```typescript
   sendPriceReq(data) {
     return this.http.post(this.serverAddress + '/sendPriceReq', data, { headers: this.setUserAuth() })
   }
   ```

**Potential Issues for Bug #2:**

1. **Toast will only show IF:** At least one vendor row has `req_status == null` (unset request status). If all selected vendors have `req_status` already set, the loop completes without any API calls, but the toast will **still appear** (line 3943).

2. **No toast if:** The `sendPriceReq` API call fails/errors — there is no error handler wrapping the `firstValueFrom()` call, so the promise rejects and execution may halt before reaching line 3943.

3. **Button visibility:** The Reminder button only appears when `ReminderSelectVisiblity = true`, which is set in `onSelectionChanged()` when `selectedRows.length > 0`. However, the button visibility depends on whether rows are **selected** (checkbox checked), not just visible.

---

### Files to Investigate Further for Bug #2:

- Check browser console for `sendPriceReq` API errors
- Verify that rows are actually being selected (checkbox state)
- Check backend logs for `/sendPriceReq` endpoint handling
- Confirm vendor rows have `req_status == null` (the filter condition on line 2923)
